</div><h3 id="2-grep----file-pattern-searcher">2. grep &ndash; file pattern searcher</h3>
<p>grep stands for “global regular expression print”. It searches files for lines that match a pattern and returns the results. It is case sensitive.</p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span><span class="lnt">2
</span><span class="lnt">3
</span><span class="lnt">4
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">grep <span class="s2">&#34;Apple&#34;</span> fruit.txt
grep -i <span class="s2">&#34;Apple&#34;</span> fruit.txt <span class="c1">#-i:case insensitive</span>
grep -R <span class="s2">&#34;Apple&#34;</span> ~/Documents/fruit <span class="c1"># -R: recursive</span>

</code></pre></td></tr></table>
